description.narrative: The Government of Romania has an increased capacity to provide technical and financial assistance, to support horizontal cooperation and to use its official development assistance resources for the rights of children and adolescents., which contributes to Communication And Advocacy, Cross-Sectoral - Human Rights, Cross-Sectoral - Other Programme Areas, Evaluation, Research. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Romania increasingly contributes to regional and global efforts to advance child rights and child-related Sustainable Development Goals with its experience, expertise and resources.

description.narrative: Romania continued to advocate for child participation within the European Union (EU) and beyond. Children mobilized by UNICEF developed capacity and skills by contributing to several international initiatives and events, sharing their experience and connecting with their peers from around the globe. The ‘minimum package of services’ (MPS) for children and families promoted by UNICEF was acknowledged by the EU to be a critical component of its ‘Child Guarantee’ framework. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/01/2022
